<div class="dablink">"Trial marriage" redirects here. For more information, see <a href="/wiki/Betrothal" title="Betrothal">betrothal</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:322px;"><a href="/wiki/File:HandFastingKnot-1.jpg" class="image" title="An example of a handfasting knot where each wedding guest has tied a ribbon around the clasped hands of the couple"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/ca/HandFastingKnot-1.jpg" width="320" height="307" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">An example of a handfasting knot where each wedding guest has tied a ribbon around the clasped hands of the couple</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Handfasting</b> is a traditional <a href="/wiki/European" title="European">European</a> ceremony of (temporary or permanent) <a href="/wiki/Betrothal" title="Betrothal">betrothal</a> or <a href="/wiki/Wedding" title="Wedding">wedding</a>. It is common in Celtic and Slavic countries.</p>
<p>The term is derived from the verb <i>to handfast</i>, used in <a href="/wiki/Middle_English" title="Middle English">Middle</a> to <a href="/wiki/Early_Modern_English" title="Early Modern English">Early Modern English</a> for the making of a <a href="/wiki/Contract_of_marriage" title="Contract of marriage" class="mw-redirect">contract of marriage</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
